Why make ube mochi pancakes 🥞 or waffles 🧇 when you could make butter mochi? These bars of gooey goodness have a coconutty, ube flavor and chewy texture I’m obsessed with.

Ingredients
1 box @traderjoes Ube Mochi Pancake & Waffle Mix
½ cup sugar
Pinch of salt
 1 ¼ cup coconut milk 
1 cup water
2 large eggs 
5 tbsp melted butter
1 tsp ube flavoring

Recipe
1. Preheat the oven to 350F. 
2. Spray nonstick spray in an 8x8 baking pan.
3. Mix dry ingredients in a large bowl with a whisk.
4. Add coconut milk, water, eggs, melted butter, and ube flavoring.
5. Whisk until smooth. 
6. Pour into a baking pan. 
7. Bake at 350F for around 70 minutes.

💡 I got this recipe from @erikavtun!

This is genuinely one of the most wholesome moments 🫶 I’ve experienced in a grocery store and of course I had to share this banana bread 🍌 recipe with ya’ll 👇

Produce Department Manager’s Banana Bread Recipe (from @sprouts) 

Ingredients:
2 cups all-purpose flour
1 ½ teaspoons baking soda
½ teaspoon salt
4 overripe bananas
1 cup sugar
¾ cup unsalted butter (1 ½ sticks), melted & cooled
2 large eggs
1 teaspoon vanilla extract

Instructions:
1. Preheat the oven to 350 degrees.
2. Lightly grease the baking pan.
3. Combine flour, baking soda and salt in a large bowl.
4. With an electric mixer, mix 2 bananas and sugar together in a separate bowl (3 mins).
5. Add melted butter, eggs, and vanilla to banana/sugar mixture, mix well.
6. Fold in dry ingredients (do not over mix).
7. Mash two other bananas and then add to the bowl (do not over mix).
8. Pour batter into a greased pan and bake for 1 hour 15 mins. Bread should be golden brown and insert a toothpick (toothpick should come out dry).
9. Let cool for at least 10 mins before serving.

Add chocolate chips and/or any other favorite items!
